# Implementation Plan - Phase 5: Payment Gateway Integration

This plan outlines the design and changes to integrate Stripe and PayPal payment checkouts, webhook endpoints, and a refund management system with entitlement rollbacks.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - **Mock/Sandbox Fallback**: To ensure the codebase is functional out-of-the-box, the APIs will automatically fallback to a beautiful, local simulated checkout flow if valid Stripe/PayPal environment keys are missing.
> - **Stripe Checkout Sessions**: We use Stripe hosted checkout page to avoid handling PCI compliance elements locally.
> - **PayPal REST API**: We will directly use PayPal's v2 Checkout API via `requests` instead of any outdated SDK packages.
> - **Entitlement Rollback**: Refunding a payment will mark the `Payment` as `REFUNDED` and set the student's corresponding `Enrollment` `is_active` to `False`.

## Open Questions
None at this stage. The requirements are fully aligned with industry best practices for DRF + React e-commerce checkouts.

